This paper is primarily focused on improving the performance of deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for image classification tasks, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of privileged information to enhance the diversity of representations learned by the CNN, which is a topic related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the proposed method involves optimizing the network's weights to learn untangled representations, which is a topic related to neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper presents experimental results on benchmark datasets, which is a topic related to multimedia (cs.MM).
